10  Appendix 3 
OUTLINE TERMS OF REFERENCE FOR CONSULTANTS 

A.  Team Leader (domestic, 18 person-months) 
1.  The team leader will have at least 10 years experience in project management, public 
sector planning and developmental management, as well as capacity building and procurement.  
The  team  leader  will  also  have  experience  of  having  worked  with  other  international  aid 
agencies.  
2.  The team leader’s key responsibilities are to 
(i)  map Government and ADB’s project start-up processes and procedures; 
(ii)  conduct a diagnostic study of Government and ADB’s operational policies and 
procedures from the perspective of identifying key factors responsible for start-up 
delays in projects; 
(iii)  design a pilot activity for supporting the Economic Affairs Division (EAD) and 
provincial planning and development departments (P&DDs) in developing and 
implementing an effective monitoring, follow up, and facilitation system for the 
different start-up stages of projects;  
(iv)  prepare an implementation plan to reduce start-up delays in projects; 
(v)  support EAD in carrying out the implementation plan and supervise and facilitate 
its implementation at the provincial level; 
(vi)  support executing agencies (EAs) at the federal level in operationalizing and 
strengthening of core project management units (CPMUs); 
(vii)  assess needs for capacity building of EAD and facilitate and supervise similar 
needs assessment for the Foreign Aid sections in the provincial P&DDs; 
(viii)  design and implement capacity building activities; 
(ix)  organize, coordinate, and document meetings and dissemination and capacity 
building workshops with stakeholders;  
(x)  coordinate project activities at the federal and provincial level; 
(xi)   supervise and coordinate the activities of consultants team; 
(xii)  coordinate to the greatest extent possible with development partners; and  
(xii)  prepare the inception report, quarterly progress reports, and final report. 

3.  The key deliverables are: (i) diagnostic Study of start-up delays in development projects; 
(ii)  an  implementation  Plan  for  streamlining  procedures  to  reduce  start-up  delays  in 
development  projects;  (iii)  improved  project  administration  manuals  (PAMs)  and  other 
documentation as necessary for use by project management staff of EAs and PMUs; and (iv) 
inception Report, mid-term progress report, and final TA report.
